+{"parentUuid":"b13435d9-7db7-434c-a2f2-8539567452d8","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspace","sessionId":"ec0f857e-1057-4a39-9046-6093133575df","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"goofy-sleeping-willow","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q8CMVRvuT9NZZmrVNvzvqv","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of the entire codebase structure and requirements.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the entire codebase. Here's everything you need to know:\n\n---\n\n### 1. FULL PROJECT STRUCTURE\n\n```\n/workspace\n├── src/\n│   └── core/\n│       ├── types.ts       - Core interfaces and types\n│       ├── engine.ts      - BuildEngine with DAG plugin system\n│       ├── templates.ts   - Default and list template factories\n│       └── index.ts       - Public exports\n├── src/plugins/           - Plugin implementations (8 files to create)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts       - 15 existing core tests\n│   └── plugins/           - 8 test files (one per plugin)\n├── package.json           - Dependencies and scripts\n├── tsconfig.json          - TypeScript configuration\n└── vitest.config.ts       - Test runner configuration\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. PLUGIN INTERFACE (from `/workspace/src/core/types.ts`)\n\n**All plugins must implement this interface:**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];      // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Types:**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;           // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. BUILD ENGINE DETAILS (`/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`)\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `registerPlugin(plugin)` - adds plugin to execution chain\n- `registerTemplate(template)` - adds template by name\n- `resolvePluginOrder()` - topological sort of plugins using DAG\n- `build(files)` - main build execution:\n  1. Calls `beforeBuild` hooks for all plugins (in dependency order)\n  2. Applies `transformContent` hooks to each file sequentially per plugin\n  3. Renders templates for each file\n  4. Calls `afterBuild` hooks for all plugins (in dependency order)\n- `getPlugins()`, `getTemplates()` - accessors\n\n**Execution Order:** Dependency resolution uses topological sort with circular dependency detection and missing dependency detection.\n\n---\n\n### 4. ALL TEST FILES (60 NEW TESTS + 15 EXISTING)\n\n#### **A. CORE TESTS (15 tests in `/workspace/tests/core.test.ts`)**\n\n1. ✅ Registers plugins\n2. ✅ Registers templates\n3. ✅ Builds with default template and renders HTML\n4. ✅ Builds with list template and renders list HTML\n5. ✅ Outputs raw content when no matching template\n6. ✅ Calls plugin beforeBuild hook\n7. ✅ Calls plugin transformContent hook to transform files\n8. ✅ Calls plugin afterBuild hook\n9. ✅ Executes plugins in dependency order\n10. ✅ Throws on circular dependency\n11. ✅ Throws on missing dependency\n12. ✅ Applies multiple plugins transformContent in order\n13. ✅ Provides shared data store in build context\n14. ✅ Retains file metadata through build\n15. ✅ Produces empty output for empty file list\n\n---\n\n#### **B. MARKDOWN-EXT PLUGIN TESTS** (`/workspace/tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts`)\n\n**Plugin:** `createMarkdownExtPlugin()`  \n**Hook:** `transformContent`  \n**Dependencies:** None\n\n**Tests (8):**\n1. ✅ Converts basic markdown to HTML\n   - Input: `'# Hello\\n\\nThis is a **bold** paragraph.'`\n   - Expected: Contains `<h1>`, `Hello`, `<strong>bold</strong>`\n\n2. ✅ Handles footnotes with `[^1]` syntax\n   - Input: `'Some text[^1] here.\\n\\n[^1]: This is the footnote.'`\n   - Expected: Contains `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n\n3. ✅ Renders footnote section at bottom\n   - Input: `'Text[^1] and more[^2].\\n\\n[^1]: First note.\\n[^2]: Second note.'`\n   - Expected: `<section class=\"footnotes\">`, `<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>`, `<li id=\"fn-2\">Second note.</li>`\n\n4. ✅ Converts `:::note` container to admonition div\n   - Input: `':::note\\nThis is a note.\\n:::'`\n   - Expected: `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">This is a note.</div>`\n\n5. ✅ Converts `:::warning` container\n   - Input: `':::warning\\nBe careful!\\n:::'`\n   - Expected: `<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">Be careful!</div>`\n\n6. ✅ Converts `:::tip` container\n   - Input: `':::tip\\nHelpful hint.\\n:::'`\n   - Expected: `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">Helpful hint.</div>`\n\n7. ✅ Preserves existing HTML in content\n8. ✅ Handles empty content\n\n---\n\n#### **C. ASSET-PIPELINE PLUGIN TESTS** (`/workspace/tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts`)\n\n**Plugin:** `createAssetPipelinePlugin()`  \n**Hook:** `transformContent`  \n**Dependencies:** None\n\n**Tests (8):**\n1. ✅ Rewrites relative image URLs to `/assets/` path\n   - Input: `'<img src=\"./image.png\" alt=\"test\">'`\n   - Expected: `'<img src=\"/assets/image.png\"'>`\n\n2. ✅ Rewrites relative link URLs to `/assets/` path\n   - Input: `'<a href=\"./doc.pdf\">Download