es missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n   - Expected: `assetPaths = []` when no asset manifest\n\n---\n\n### 5. DEPENDENCIES & SCRIPTS\n\n**From `/workspace/package.json`:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/marked\": \"^5.0.2\",\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"marked\": \"^17.0.2\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Dependencies:**\n- `marked` - Markdown parsing library\n- `express` - Web framework (for dev-server plugin)\n\n---\n\n### 6. TYPESCRIPT CONFIGURATION\n\n**From `/workspace/tsconfig.json`:**\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: Node16\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Declaration files generated\n- Output: `./dist`\n- Root: `./src`\n\n---\n\n### 7. WAVE-BASED DEPENDENCY STRUCTURE\n\n**Wave 1 (No dependencies):**\n- markdown-ext\n- asset-pipeline\n- syntax-highlight\n- taxonomy\n\n**Wave 2 (Depend on Wave 1):**\n- rss-feed (depends: markdown-ext, taxonomy)\n- search-index (depends: markdown-ext, syntax-highlight)\n\n**Wave 3 (Depend on Wave 2):**\n- sitemap (depends: taxonomy, rss-feed)\n- dev-server (depends: asset-pipeline, search-index)\n\n---\n\n### 8. CRITICAL IMPLEMENTATION NOTES\n\n**Each plugin must:**\n1. Export a factory function: `createXxxPlugin(): Plugin`\n2. Have correct name, version, and dependencies array\n3. Implement required hooks (beforeBuild, transformContent, or afterBuild)\n4. Store data in `ctx.data` using consistent key names:\n   - `asset-manifest`: `{ assets: string[] }`\n   - `taxonomy-tags`: `Map<string, ContentFile[]>`\n   - `dev-server-config`: DevServerConfig object\n5. Use `marked` library for markdown conversion (if needed)\n6. Handle edge cases: empty content, missing data, no tags, etc.\n\n**Build Order Matters:**\n- The topological sort ensures plugins run in dependency order\n- Data from earlier plugins (via `ctx.data`) is available to later plugins\n- Content transformations are cumulative\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive analysis covers every test requirement, every plugin interface, and all dependencies you need to implement the 8 plugins successfully!"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: afec437737cec1338 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 40728\ntool_uses: 19\nduration_ms: 57401</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"694bc2be-dd87-49a9-872f-86b275a3f356","timestamp":"2026-03-10T16:15:59.557Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The full project structure (all files)\n2. The Plugin interface from src/core/types.ts\n3. The build engine in src/core/\n4. All test files in tests/plugins/ - read every single one completely\n5. The existing tests in tests/core.test.ts\n6. Package.json for dependencies and scripts\n7. tsconfig.json\n\nRead ALL files completely. This is critical - I need every detail of every test file to implement the plugins correctly.","agentId":"afec437737cec1338","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of the entire codebase structure and requirements.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the entire codebase. Here's everything you need to know:\n\n---\n\n### 1. FULL PROJECT STRUCTURE\n\n```\n/workspace\n├── src/\n│   └── core/\n│       ├── types.ts       - Core interfaces and types\n│       ├── engine.ts      - BuildEngine with DAG plugin system\n│       ├── templates.ts   - Default and list template factories\n│       └── index.ts       - Public exports\n├── src/plugins/           - Plugin implementations (8 files to create)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts       - 15 existing core tests\n│   └── plugins/           - 8 test files (one per plugin)\n├── package.json           - Dependencies and scripts\n├── tsconfig.json          - TypeScript configuration\n└── vitest.config.ts       - Test runner configuration\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. PLUGIN INTERFACE (from `/workspace/src/core/types.ts`)\n\n**All plugins must implement this interface:**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];      // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Types:**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;           // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. BUILD ENGINE DETAILS (`/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`)\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `registerPlugin(plugin)` - adds plugin to execution chain\n- `registerTemplate(template)` - adds template by name\n- `resolvePluginOrder()` - topological sort of plugins using DAG\n- `build(files)` - main build execution:\n  1. Calls `beforeBuild` hooks for all plugins (in dependency order)\n  2. Applies `transformContent` hooks to each file sequentially per plugin\n  3. Renders templates for each file\n  4. Calls `afterBuild` hooks for all plugins (in dependency order)\n- `getPlugins()`, `getTemplates()` - accessors\n\n**Execution Order:** Dependency resolution uses topological sort with circular dependency detection and missing dependency detection.\n\